properties.areaDesc: Coastal Waters from Point Pinos to Point Piedras Blancas California out to 10 nm
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 4 at 2:38PM PST until January 5 at 9:00AM PST by NWS San Francisco CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, northwest winds 20 to 30 kt with
gusts up to 35 kt and seas 8 to 12 feet at 13 seconds
expected. For the Small Craft Advisory, northwest winds 15 to
25 kt with gusts up to 30 kt and seas 9 to 11 feet at 13
seconds expected.

* WHERE...Coastal Waters from Point Pinos to Point Piedras
Blancas California out to 10 nm.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 9 PM this evening to 9 AM
PST Sunday. For the Small Craft Advisory, until 9 PM PST this
evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM PST THIS EVENING... ...GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO 9 AM PST SUNDAY
